    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-07-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="257" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-07-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.
                                (Received July 17.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I transmitted to my Government a copy of
                            your note of May 25 last in relation to the revised regulations for
                            preventing collisions at sea, and I have the honor to inform you that I
                            have been instructed by the Earl of Kimberley to state to you with
                            reference to the concluding paragraph of the letter from Mr. Wike,
                            inclosed in your note, that no alteration will be made for the present
                            in the regulations relating to fishing vessels’ lights. The only
                            regulations repealed by the forthcoming British Order in Council will be
                            those contained in Articles i to ix and xi to xxvii, inclusive, of the
                            schedule to the Order in Council of August 11, 1884.</p>
                <p>The date of the new Order in Council can not at present be fixed, as the
                            principal maritime powers have not yet signified their acceptance of the
                            regulations.</p>
                <p>I have the honor, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
